# Frontend Patterns (Next.js 16 + React 19)

## App Router conventions
- Server Components by default — do NOT add 'use client' unless you need:
  - onClick, onChange, or other event handlers
  - useState, useEffect, or other hooks
  - browser-only APIs (window, localStorage)
- 'use cache' for any data that can be cached (Next.js 16 feature) — do NOT use fetch revalidate for cacheable data
- All async Dynamic APIs (cookies, headers, params) must be awaited

## Tailwind v4 and PostCSS
- postcss.config.mjs is REQUIRED (use .mjs extension); plugin: @tailwindcss/postcss
- @import "tailwindcss" in globals.css (NOT the three @tailwind directives from v3)
- @import "tw-animate-css" in globals.css — use tw-animate-css classes for animations, not tailwindcss-animate or custom keyframes
- @source directive in globals.css pointing at packages/ui (and any shared UI) so Tailwind v4 scans those paths
- Design tokens are CSS custom properties in @theme {} blocks
- No tailwind.config.js — customisation goes in CSS
- Never use theme() function in CSS — use var(--token-name)

## Data fetching
- Fetch in Server Components — never in useEffect
- Use createSupabaseServerClient from @agency/database in Server Components and Server Actions
- Pass fetched data down as props to Client Components
- WRONG: 'use client' + useEffect + fetch or Supabase in a component. CORRECT: async Server Component that calls createSupabaseServerClient(cookies()) and awaits .from('table').select(); pass result as props to children.

## Components
- All shared components live in packages/ui, not in apps
- Use cn() from @agency/ui for all className merging
- shadcn/ui components are in packages/ui/src/components
- Structure: Atomic Design — atoms/, molecules/, organisms/ under packages/ui/src/components; see packages/ui/src/components/README.md and docs/architecture/ARCHITECTURE.md §Component structure
- WRONG: hardcoded colors (bg-[#hex], style={{ color: '...' }}), or theme() in CSS. CORRECT: cn() and token-based classes (bg-brand-primary, text-text-default, border-border-default).
